Iraqi troops, led by 350 tanks, crossed the border early Thursday and quickly seized  government buildings in Kuwait City.
They were also sweeping through southern  Kuwaiti oilfields.
Iraq has a population of 17 million, and boasts the Arab world's most  battled-trained army.
Sixty percent of Kuwait's inhabitants are foreigners.
Iraq had  accused Kuwait of stealing oil from a disputed border area, and forcing down oil prices  through overproduction.
President Bush denounced the invasion as "naked aggression".
United States naval  vessels were diverted toward the Persian Gulf.
Oil prices soared in anticipation of a  reduced supply of oil.  
